    {
      "craigslist": {
        "url": "https://sfbay.craigslist.org/eby/apa/d/oakland-bright-studio/7945061259.html",
        "posting_id": "7945061259",
        "title": "Bright Studio",
        "price": 1650,
        "price_text": "$1,650",
        "room": 0,
        "area": "440",
        "loft": "1",
        "location": "400 Santa Clara Ave. near Lake Park Ave.",
        "full_address": "400 Santa Clara Ave. near Lake Park Ave.",
        "locality": "",
        "geocode_query": "400 Santa Clara Ave. near Lake Park Ave.",
        "description": "QR Code Link to This Post Bright studio with HARDWOOD FLOORS is on a first level of a QUIET , 28 unit, early 1920s Spanish Revival building (with ELEVATOR ). Located in the GRAND LAKE THEATRE NEIGHBORHOOD , just 2 blocks from Lake Merritt. Accessible to SHOPPING (Trader Joe’s, Safeway, Walgreens, Ace Hardware, Oakanna), RESTAURANTS & CAFES, PUBLIC TRANSPORTATION SERVICES (AC Transit, BART and RideShare departure locations ) and just around the corner is the Oakland-Grand Lake Farmers Market (Saturdays). SEPARATE KITCHEN which includes a GAS STOVE/OVEN, and FROST-FREE REFRIGERATOR and a small area for dining. A large WALK-IN CLOSET with over-head shelving and built-in dresser as well as an additional SMALL CLOSET for all your storage needs. Windowed bathroom with a shower over full-sized tub. An integrated, SECURE, electronically-coded entry system gives you the option of letting your guests inside conveniently from your phone and a ceiling fan helps complement this charming studio apartment. Included , in the utilities, are GAS, WATER, STEAM HEAT and WASTE/RECYCLING/COMPOST. All you are responsible for is electricity and ISP service ( Sonic Fiber-Optic Cable and/or Xfinity Cable ) if needed. Coin-operated washers and dryers are available 24/7 in the LAUNDRY ROOM. Parking is available on the street. PAID PARKING on property when available with sign-up on Waiting List. This is a minimum of a one (1) year lease which automatically rolls over to a Month-to-Month term after the first year of residency. Your pet is always welcome here. St. Maarten Apts. allows you to provide a safe and secure home for 1 (one) small dog or cat, and the best part of all— no pet deposit required. To submit an application you must bring $45 ( CASH or make a Zelle® transfer ) for a required Credit Report fee (we will gladly accept a current, complete CR you provide in lieu of CR fee). Rank is determined by the order that completed applications are received. Once approved, a Cashier's Check/Money Order/Zelle® transfer must be remitted within 48 hours (2 days) upon receiving acceptance notification in the amount of $3,050 (1st Month’s Rent + Security Deposit). Scheduled appointments can be made preferably by calling/texting show contact info between the hours of 9 a.m. – 8 p.m., Monday thru Saturday. Showings can be made for Sundays by making special arrangements. ST. MAARTEN APARTMENTS is located at 400 Santa Clara Ave., Oakland. Thank you for your consideration and taking interest in ST. MAARTEN APARTMENTS. ** Please note, email inquiries will not be answered at this time. Feel free to call/text further questions and schedule appointments. Please, do not email your requests.**",
