        "description": "QR Code Link to This Post A Beautifully remodeled 1 BD/1BA (650 SQ FT) Craftsman triplex in Berkeley's vibrant Gilman / Westbrae district. This is the rear unit of a front/back duplex. There is a detached adu in the rear. See floor plan image(1340 unit). No upstairs or downstairs neighbors! The unit features hardwoods, quartz + Maple kitchen counters, gas range, Range hood, fireplace, central heat, washer and dryer, dual pane windows, walk in closet in living room, large hall closet, bedroom closet, keyed gated entry. There is a large living room and dining area. Central heat in the unit with vents in each room. Back yard and Side yard garden area. Very quiet property. The apartment is within 5 minute walking distance to all Gilman district amenities including, to Whole Foods, Berkeley Natural market, Tokyo Fish Market, Philz Coffee, Ashkenaz, Acme Bread, Picante, REI, North Face, Picante, Westbrae Bier Garten, Bartavelle Coffee and Wine bar, Berkeley Bagels, Monterey Market and much more. 14 blocks to North Berkeley Bart. 1 block to rapid bus line. Short Lyft ride or bike ride to campus. Non permit street parking is bountiful. Available August 1, or possibly a little earlier if needed. 1 year lease which becomes month to month after 1 year. Landlord pays garbage only. Move-in cost is 1st months rent + deposit. 1 Year lease which becomes month to month after 1 year. Free onsite laundry.",
